question_text: A user reports frequent paper jams when printing double-sided jobs from tray 2. Which two factors should a technician investigate first? (Select two)
answer_options: Paper weight compatibility with duplex printing
Paper tray alignment with the feed rollers
Incorrect IP address assigned to the printer
correct_answer: Paper weight compatibility with duplex printing
Paper tray alignment with the feed rollers
explanation: Double-sided printing requires specific paper weights and precise alignment of trays and rollers. Incorrect configurations can result in jams during duplex operation.
